                            <comment id="11678" author="juergen.hoeller" created="Sat, 4 Dec 2004 03:37:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for spotting this! I&apos;ve just fixed it through a getType call for the give bean name (which correctly determines the type of the returned object, even for child bean definitions that inherit the bean class from the parent).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Juergen&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="11780" author="jstuyts" created="Tue, 14 Dec 2004 00:16:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Because of these changes I now get an NPE. Here is a simple test case to reproduce it. This used to work using Spring 1.1.2:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BeanFactory beanFactory = new XmlBeanFactory(new FileSystemResource(&quot;beans.xml&quot;));&lt;br/&gt;
System.out.println(beanFactory.getBean(&quot;documentBuilder&quot;));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;!DOCTYPE beans PUBLIC &quot;-//SPRING//DTD BEAN//EN&quot; &quot;http://www.springframework.org/dtd/spring-beans.dtd&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;beans&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;documentBuilderFactory&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
    class=&quot;javax.xml.parsers.DocumentBuilderFactory&quot; factory-method=&quot;newInstance&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;/bean&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
  &amp;lt;bean id=&quot;documentBuilder&quot; factory-bean=&quot;documentBuilderFactory&quot; factory-method=&quot;newDocumentBuilder&quot;/&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/beans&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
